tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a full aesthetic overhaul, moving
  from a generic look to a calming, professional sleep-themed design. This
  involved a new color palette, improved layout, polished UI components,
  consistent section styling, and a fix for a console error.
overview: "The user wanted to transform their sleep questionnaire app's
  aesthetics from a generic appearance to a beautiful, professional, and calming
  experience. The approach involved a multi-phase redesign: first, a new
  sleep-themed color palette was introduced, followed by a significant overhaul
  of the main form layout, including decorative background elements, a
  redesigned progress indicator, and a subtle star pattern on card headers. All
  core UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and progress bars
  were polished with improved visual feedback and transitions. The initial
  welcome screen was enhanced with a hero section and feature cards. Crucially,
  consistent styling was applied across all 14 questionnaire sections, replacing
  old gray boxes with new card-style groupings and themed typography. A console
  error regarding null input values was also identified and fixed by ensuring
  inputs receive empty strings instead of null. Finally, based on a self-review,
  alert components were re-themed to align with the new palette, and section
  border opacities were adjusted for better definition. The outcome is a
  visually cohesive and professional application that effectively conveys a
  sense of calm and trustworthiness."
